{{Infobox journal | title = Journal of Hispanic Higher Education | cover = Journal of Hispanic Higher Education Journal Front Cover.jpg | editor = Esther Elena López-Mulnix | discipline = [[Education]] | former_names = | abbreviation = J. Hisp. High. Educ. | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] | country = | frequency = Quarterly | history = 2002-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = 2010 | website = http://www.uk.sagepub.com/journals/Journal201513?siteId=sage-uk&prodTypes=any&q=Journal+of+Hispanic+Higher+Education&fs=1 | link1 = http://jhh.sagepub.com/content/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://jhh.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 1538-1927 | eISSN = | OCLC = 48660300 | LCCN = }}
'''''The Journal of Hispanic Higher Education''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that publishes papers four times a year in the fields of [[education]] and [[ethnic interests]]. The journal's [[Editor-in-Chief|editor]] is Esther Elena López-Mulnix, PhD. It has been in publication since 2002 and is currently published by [[SAGE Publications]].
== Scope == ''The Journal of Hispanic Higher Education'' is devoted to the advancement of knowledge and understanding of issues at Hispanic-serving institutions. The journal is interdisciplinary and publishes both quantitative and qualitative articles that specifically relate to issues of interest at Hispanic-serving institutions of higher learning worldwide.
== Abstracting and indexing == ''The Journal of Hispanic Higher Education'' is abstracted and indexed in the following databases: :* [[Contents Pages in Education]] :* [[Educational Administration Abstracts]] :* [[Educational Research Abstracts Online]] :* [[SCOPUS]] :* [[Social Services Abstracts]]
== External links == * {{Official website|1=http://jhh.sagepub.com/}}
