{{Infobox company | name = State School Teachers Union of Western Australia | logo = State_Schoo_Teachers_Union_of_WA_Logo.png | logo_size = 300 | logo_caption = SSTUWA Logo | image = SSTUWA building on Thomas Street.jpg | image_size = 300 | image_caption = SSTUWA Building in [[West Perth, Western Australia|West Perth]] | location = 1 West St, West Perth, Western Australia 6005 | type = Industrial Union | trading_name = SSTUWA | key_people = {{Unbulleted list|Pat Byrne (President)|Mary Franklin (General Secretary)}} | | website = {{url|www.sstuwa.org.au}} }}
The '''State School Teachers Union of W.A. (Inc.)''' (SSTUWA) is an [[Australia]]n trade union. It represents teachers working in the Western Australian state school system<ref>{{cite web |title=A strong voice in the workplace and within the community |url=https://www.sstuwa.org.au/about-home |website=SSTUWA |publisher=SSTUWA |accessdate=25 September 2018}}</ref>, which includes public schools and [[Technical and further education|TAFE]] institutes<ref>{{cite web |title=SSTUWA: STATE SCHOOL TEACHERS' UNION OF WESTERN AUSTRALIA |url=https://www.unionswa.com.au/state_school_teachers_union_of_western_australia_sstuwa |website=UnionsWA |publisher=UnionsWA |accessdate=27 September 2018 |ref=4}}</ref>, and is affiliated with the federal [[Australian Education Union]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Hopgood |first1=Susan |title=Organisation |url=http://www.aeufederal.org.au/about/branches |website=Australian Education Union (AEU) |publisher=AEU |accessdate=25 September 2018 |ref=2}}</ref> It has been in continuous existence since 1898.<ref>{{cite web |title=Volume 47.7 - September 2018 |url=http://westernteacher.realviewdigital.com/?i=Volume47.7-September2018#folio=2 |website=Western Teacher Magazine |publisher=SSTUWA |accessdate=25 September 2018 |ref=3}}</ref>
== Purpose == The SSTUWA has a number of roles, including * Negotiating conditions of employment and salaries, with the [[Department of Education (Western Australia)|Department of Education]], for public school teachers working under the ''School Education Act Employees' Agreement (Teachers and Administrators)''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Schools General Agreement 2017 endorsed by members |url=https://www.sstuwa.org.au/news-home/2018/june/schools-general-agreement-2017-endorsed-members |website=SSTUWA - News |publisher=SSTUWA |accessdate=27 September 2018 |ref=5}}</ref> * Negotiating conditions of employment and salaries for TAFE lecturers working under the ''Western Australian TAFE Lectures' General Agreement''.<ref>{{cite web |title=TAFE |url=https://www.sstuwa.org.au/members-home/tafe |website=SSTUWA |publisher=SSTUWA |accessdate=27 September 2018 |ref=6}}</ref> * Advocating for improvements in the Western Australian state school system at a local, [[Government of Western Australia|state]] and [[Federal government of Australia|federal]] level.<ref>{{cite web |title=About |url=https://www.sstuwa.org.au/about-home |website=SSTUWA |accessdate=27 September 2018 |ref=7}}</ref>
